http://sis.berkeley.edu/student/enrollment

"If you try to enroll in two classes that have a time schedule overlap, CalCentral will alert you at the point of enrollment and give you an opportunity to submit an online request to enroll in both classes. It will take approximately one business day to process request forms. If no other restrictions prevent you from enrolling in both classes, your time conflict restriction will be waived and your enrollment will be processed."

If this doesn't happen, please contact the SIS team

I want to enroll in a DeCal that has a conflicting schedule with the lectures of CS 186. Since the lectures of CS 186 is webcast, I thought it'd be fine to miss it since I can always watch the webcast at another time. How do I go about enrolling in a DeCal through CalCentral that conflicts with the lectures of CS 186?

I have always been able to enroll with conflicting schedules before CalCentral so I thought this might be a CalCentral problem.
history.subject: Enrolling in Class That Conflict
